Day of Korea's Liberation Observed in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 25 (KCNA) -- Meetings, seminars, film shows and photo exhibitions took place in Italy, Finland, Peru, Congo, Mexico, Nepal, Malaysia and India from Aug. 4 to 13 on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of Korea's liberation.
 Roberto Gabriele, general secretary of the Movement for Peace and Socialism of Italy, said in his speech at a meeting that leader Kim Jong Il has firmly defended Korean socialism true to the will of President Kim Il Sung, frustrating the moves of the U.S.-led imperialist allied forces to stifle the DPRK. The movement will positively support the Korean people in their struggle for building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and achieving the reunification of Korea, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Alberto Moreno, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Peru "Red Motherland", noted that the world revolutionaries remember the precious exploits performed by Kim Il Sung and strive hard to learn from the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Peruvian National Independent Movement for the Free Vote Union noted at a seminar that Korean socialism is widely known to the world as a powerful socialist nation of Juche in which the independence and dignity of the popular masses are displayed to the full thanks to the outstanding Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ramon Jimenez Lopez, chairman of a District Committee of Mexico City of the Democratic Revolutionary Party of Mexico who is president of the Mexican Committee for the Study of Kimilsungism, said at a seminar that the Korean people would surely build a great prosperous powerful nation and achieve the cause of Korea's reunification in the not distant future under the leadership of Kim Jong Il identical to Kim Il Sung.
A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at a meeting held in Finland.

Anniversary of DPRK's Entry into NAM Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 25 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today dedicates a signed article to the 30th anniversary of the DPRK's entry into the Non-Aligned Movement as a full-fledge member.
 Its entry into the NAM served as an important occasion in increasing the ranks of the movement and promoting its strengthening and development and raising the external position and voice of the DPRK, the article notes, and goes on: 
 The DPRK's entry gave a fresh impetus to the Non-Aligned Movement and energy and courage to non-aligned and other developing countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With this event, the position and might of the NAM were strengthened and favorable circumstance and phase were provided to preserve the purity of the movement as the independent political forces and hasten its development and triumphant advance.
 In the days of the 6th Summit of NAM countries, the DPRK disclosed the imperialists' moves to split and sow discord among NAM members and strove for the unity and solidarity of the movement. This greatly helped save the NAM from crisis of division and ensure its progress in conformity with its noble mission and purpose. Over the past years the DPRK has exerted all possible efforts to preserve the idea and principle of the movement and its purity from every obstruction of the imperialists and ensure its unity and development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now the NAM is faced with important tasks to strengthen solidarity and cooperation among its member countries, reject any attempts to degrade its fundamental principle and political nature, and increase its action capability as a political force speaking for the South in the UN and other international arenas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK, which regards it as an iron principle of its foreign policy to invariably preserve the basic principle and idea of the NAM, will as ever fulfill its responsibility and duty for the strengthening and development of the movement for global independence and the NAM, the article concludes.

Anniversary of Kim Il Sung's Famous Work Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 25 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Thursday dedicates a signed article to the 45th anniversary of the publication of President Kim Il Sung's famous work "The People's Army Is a Communist School".
 The President in the work published on August 25, Juche 49 (1960) re-clarified the revolutionary character and working class character of the People's Army and set forth tasks to be fulfilled to strengthen it into invincible armed forces fully prepared politically and ideologically and ways to implement them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President's Juche-oriented idea and cause of building revolutionary armed forces have been successfully carried forward by leader Kim Jong Il, the article says, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The last several decades since the publication of the work have been a period in which revolutionary changes have taken place in the ideological and political work of the People's Army and its politico-ideological advantages have been fully displayed under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has exerted utmost efforts for increasing the politico-ideological might of the revolutionary armed forces over the last decade, in particular, holding higher the banner of Songun to cope with the grave situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to his dynamic Songun leadership, the People's Army has demonstrated its might as a vanguard standard-bearer taking the lead in upholding the socialist cause and the first-line guard and death-defying corps that absolutely trust the Workers' Party of Korea and the leader and follow them with loyalty in any storm and stress.
 The invincible might of the People's Army has been fully displayed in devotedly defending the headquarters of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The People's Army is the loyal vanguard which regards it as its biggest mission and the general goal of all its struggles and activities to devotedly defend the headquarters of the revolution headed by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This invincible might of the People's Army finds a most vivid manifestation in cherishing socialism as their fixed faith in struggles. This is clearly proved by the fact that a revolutionary sound fighting trait and work style are prevailing in the entire army.

All Koreans Called upon to Remain True to Idea of "By Our Nation Itself" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 25 (KCNA) -- The idea of "By our nation itself" reflecting the steadfast spirit of national independence and noble patriotism serves as a powerful ideological weapon inspiring the Koreans to build a reunified powerful nation, providing a foundation of a reunified great prosperous powerful nation and making it possible to achieve eternal prosperity. Rodong Sinmun Thursday says this in a signed article.
 It goes on: The idea of "By our nation itself" gives full rein to the spirit of national independence which the Koreans regard as its life and soul and thus enables them to lay a solid groundwork for building an independent reunified powerful nation.
 National independence constitutes a basic principle which should be held fast to not only in the struggle for the cause of national reunification but in the whole course of hewing out the destiny of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea of "By our nation itself" is mainly based on the spirit of national independence calling upon all the Koreans in the north and the south who are responsible for solving the issue to reunify the country not in reliance upon outside forces but by their concerted efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea, by nature, never allows outsiders to interfere in settling the issue of the nation. The main problem in achieving the country's reunification will be settled and a groundwork be laid for building an independent unified state only when the Koreans embody the idea of "By our nation itself" which calls for settling all problems by the concerted efforts of the Koreans, guided by the idea, in line with the will and interests of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea of "By our nation itself" gives fullest play to patriotism enshrined in the hearts of all the fellow countrymen to provide a powerful engine for building a reunified strong nation.

River-Crossing Contest Marks Day of Youth
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 25 (KCNA) -- A River Taedong crossing contest of school youth and children here took place on Aug. 24 to mark the day of the youth.
 The contest brought together at least 1,300 good boy and girl swimmers from middle schools in the districts and counties of Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A ceremony was held on the bank of the river to kick off the contest in front of Kim Il Sung Square. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the swimmers began crossing the river full of fighting spirit, the spectators sent a warm applause to them. They cheered the swimmers crossing the river in the spirit of collectivism and perseverance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the contest, citations and prizes were awarded to the successful teams.
  Among the spectators were Kim Jin Ha, secretary of the Pyongyang City Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, and officials concerned and school youth and children in the city.

Far-infrared Stupe Treatment Device
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 25 (KCNA) -- Bath-House No. 1, Children's Health Complex attached to the Mangyongdae Schoolchildren's Palace and other units in Pyongyang are crowded with many people for their service of far-infrared high temperature sauna.
 Among them are hypertensives and other patients who are not allowed to take sauna.
 An employee of Bath-House No. 1 told KCNA that the far-infrared high temperature sauna gives medical treatment to the bathers without giving any physical burden to them, unlike the convection sauna causing skin pricking and blood pressure rise and the far-infrared low temperature sauna. Its secret lies in the far-infrared radiation generator, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The radiation generator won the invention priority in December 2003 and the DPRK invention patent right in August 2004. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The surface temperature of the generator is 300 degrees C. It, which generates little near-infrared rays, is a means for irradiating far-infrared rays of wavelengths best matchable to human body with high directiveness and emissivity. 
 The far-infrared rays emitted from the generator are absorbed completely in the skin to enlarge capillary vessels to the utmost in a moment and heighten perspiration speed.
 In particular, it gives stupe treatment while affecting the head a little.
 Its concentrated application to sick region makes it possible to instantly stop neuralgia, arthritis and stomach cramps. It is also good for digestive system disorders, women's diseases and circulatory diseases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sauna is possible even in open rooms with this generator. It is applicable for various purposes including medical treatment, heating and drying. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The generator, developed by researcher Ri Yong Nam, was appreciated at the international patent technology show held in Dalian, China, from August 18 to 20.
 Far-infrared radiation generators of various uses are being mass-produced by the Far-Infrared Technology Institute in Pyongyang.

New Species of Turf Bred
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 25 (KCNA) -- The Institute of City Management under the Academy of Sciences of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has succeeded in breeding a new species of turf.
 It, very viable and blight-resistant, quickly grows. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fully grown turf, 5-6 cm high, does not need to be cut. And its density is 500-600 stalks per 100 square centimeters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This turf, a clone variety, can be planted in parks, recreation grounds, football fields, golf links and gardens.
